/science/how-a-failed-attempt-to-protect-a-tablecloth-led-to-jacques-e-brandenbergers-invention-of-cellophane/articleshow/131262837.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-22T17:05:44+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131262929,imgsize-1147406.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[How streetlights may be affecting birds, bats and insects at night in ways scientists did not expect]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131260426.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/how-streetlights-may-be-affecting-birds-bats-and-insects-at-night-in-ways-scientists-did-not-expect/articleshow/131260426.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/how-streetlights-may-be-affecting-birds-bats-and-insects-at-night-in-ways-scientists-did-not-expect/articleshow/131260426.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-22T14:32:03+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131260493,imgsize-1276426.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Archaeologists found an intact Anglo-Saxon burial chamber in Essex, challenging old ‘Dark Ages’ views]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131245354.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Archaeologists unearthed the Prittlewell burial, an intact chamber revealing high-status Anglo-Saxon objects. This princely grave provides a complete archaeological context for study. The well-preserved artifacts and their arrangement showcase structured elite culture and burial traditions. This discovery challenges the 'Dark Ages' interpretation, highlighting sophisticated societies with foreign trade and organized labor in early medieval England.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/archaeologists-found-an-intact-anglo-saxon-burial-chamber-in-essex-challenging-old-dark-ages-views/articleshow/131245354.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/archaeologists-found-an-intact-anglo-saxon-burial-chamber-in-essex-challenging-old-dark-ages-views/articleshow/131245354.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-22T16:48:48+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131245370,imgsize-1584971.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Scientists say Antarctic mud revealed a rainforest near the South Pole]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131245211.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Fossils of an intact root network, pollen, and spores discovered near the South Pole reveal a temperate rainforest existed during the Cretaceous period. This ancient ecosystem, found in a sediment core from the Amundsen Sea, indicates West Antarctica was ice-free and supported dense vegetation with an average temperature of 12 degrees Celsius.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-say-antarctic-mud-revealed-a-rainforest-near-the-south-pole/articleshow/131245211.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-say-antarctic-mud-revealed-a-rainforest-near-the-south-pole/articleshow/131245211.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-22T16:00:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131245222,imgsize-1984685.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[A 13-year-old built a LEGO Braille printer to make reading more affordable]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131244151.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A 13-year-old American innovator, Shubham Banerjee, revolutionized Braille printing with Braigo, a remarkably affordable device built from Lego blocks.  This invention addresses the high cost of traditional embossers, making tactile reading accessible to more visually impaired individuals.  Braigo's simple design and focus on affordability have garnered significant attention, highlighting the power of user-centric problem-solving.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/a-13-year-old-built-a-lego-braille-printer-to-make-reading-more-affordable/articleshow/131244151.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/a-13-year-old-built-a-lego-braille-printer-to-make-reading-more-affordable/articleshow/131244151.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-22T15:32:18+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131245053,imgsize-1076232.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Quote of the day by Vietnamese Communist revolutionary leader Ho Chi Minh: “To reap a return in ten years, plant trees. To reap a return in 100, cultivate the people.”]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131260511.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/quote-of-the-day-by-vietnamese-communist-revolutionary-leader-ho-chi-minh-to-reap-a-return-in-ten-years-plant-trees-to-reap-a-return-in-100-cultivate-the-people-/articleshow/131260511.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/quote-of-the-day-by-vietnamese-communist-revolutionary-leader-ho-chi-minh-to-reap-a-return-in-ten-years-plant-trees-to-reap-a-return-in-100-cultivate-the-people-/articleshow/131260511.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-22T15:58:41+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131260498,imgsize-28914.cms"/></item></channel></rss>